{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843255316,"sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","part":{"id":"prt_d7881a3e6001mI76LwoVh4WWO9","messageID":"msg_d78818ed7001SZ6VigPRmxnlMK","sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-71ec760c21044b0ea100273b9c3c7a08","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775843255306,"end":1775843255315}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843255319,"sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","part":{"id":"prt_d788196ed001GalRMzswNaavtC","messageID":"msg_d78818ed7001SZ6VigPRmxnlMK","sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_tool-2e304ed8226e49f4b0186e98bd986c5c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"**/delta-spec*.md"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md","metadata":{"count":6,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z","time":{"start":1775843255301,"end":1775843255318}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843255333,"sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","part":{"id":"prt_d78819f46001bBL27p9198PlTH","messageID":"msg_d78818ed7001SZ6VigPRmxnlMK","sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d8601c4d301945f78d8c882d993a6656","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/common/types/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/common/types/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package types\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"errors\"\n5: \t\"time\"\n6: )\n7: \n8: const (\n9: \tAgentRuntimeKind    = \"AgentRuntime\"\n10: \tCodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n11: )\n12: \n13: var (\n14: \tErrInvalidKind       = errors.New(\"invalid kind: must be AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\")\n15: \tErrNameRequired      = errors.New(\"name is required\")\n16: \tErrNamespaceRequired = errors.New(\"namespace is required\")\n17: )\n18: \n19: type SandboxInfo struct {\n20: \tKind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n21: \tSandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n22: \tSandboxName      string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n23: \tSandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n24: \tName             string              `json:\"name\"`\n25: \tEntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n26: \tSessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n27: \tCreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n28: \tExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n29: \tStatus           string              `json:\"status\"`\n30: \tPodIP            string              `json:\"podIp,omitempty\"`\n31: \tWorkloadName     string              `json:\"workloadName,omitempty\"`\n32: \tNamespace        string              `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n33: \tLastActivityAt   time.Time           `json:\"lastActivityAt,omitempty\"`\n34: }\n35: \n36: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n37: \tPath     string `json:\"path\"`\n38: \tProtocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n39: \tEndpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n40: }\n41: \n42: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n43: \tKind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n44: \tName      string `json:\"name\"`\n45: \tNamespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n46: }\n47: \n48: func (car *CreateSandboxRequest) Validate() error {\n49: \tif car.Kind != AgentRuntimeKind && car.Kind != CodeInterpreterKind {\n50: \t\treturn ErrInvalidKind\n51: \t}\n52: \tif car.Name == \"\" {\n53: \t\treturn ErrNameRequired\n54: \t}\n55: \tif car.Namespace == \"\" {\n56: \t\treturn ErrNamespaceRequired\n57: \t}\n58: \treturn nil\n59: }\n60: \n61: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n62: \tSessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n63: \tSandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n64: \tSandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n65: \tEntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n66: }\n67: \n68: type GetSessionRequest struct {\n69: \tSessionID string `uri:\"sessionId\" binding:\"required\"`\n70: }\n71: \n72: type GetSessionResponse struct {\n73: \tSessionID    string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n74: \tSandboxID    string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n75: \tSandboxName  string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n76: \tKind         string              `json:\"kind\"`\n77: \tNamespace    string              `json:\"namespace\"`\n78: \tName         string              `json:\"name\"`\n79: \tEntryPoints  []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n80: \tLastActivity string              `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n81: \tCreatedAt    string              `json:\"createdAt\"`\n82: \tExpiresAt    string              `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n83: \tPodIP        string              `json:\"podIp,omitempty\"`\n84: }\n85: \n86: type DeleteSessionRequest struct {\n87: \tSessionID string `uri:\"sessionId\" binding:\"required\"`\n88: }\n89: \n90: type DeleteSessionResponse struct {\n91: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n92: \tDeletedAt string `json:\"deletedAt\"`\n93: }\n94: \n95: type ErrorResponse struct {\n96: \tError string `json:\"error\"`\n97: \tCode  string `json:\"code,omitempty\"`\n98: }\n\n(End of file - total 98 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package types\n\nimport (\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tAgentRuntimeKind    = \"AgentRuntime\"\n\tCodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\tErrInvalidKind       = errors.New(\"invalid kind: must be AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\")\n\tErrNameRequired      = errors.New(\"name is required\")\n\tErrNamespaceRequired = errors.New(\"namespace is required\")\n)\n\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n\tKind             string              `json:\"kind\"`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/common/types/types.go","time":{"start":1775843255304,"end":1775843255330}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775843255353,"sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","part":{"id":"prt_d7881a424001A4ypPtV6fWLnkl","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78818ed7001SZ6VigPRmxnlMK","sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":38040,"input":536,"output":129,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":37375}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775843257099,"sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","part":{"id":"prt_d7881ab08001KcHbDmbDjaEVPy","messageID":"msg_d7881a44e001zGrGozA8MnqczW","sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843260392,"sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","part":{"id":"prt_d7881b20c001gM1ljGWvVvJaFj","messageID":"msg_d7881a44e001zGrGozA8MnqczW","sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bc22b65cf9c14c5090c92910768d1f0b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 Delta Specification: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `AgentRuntime` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime type metadata and API group version\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `AgentRuntime`, and resource plural `agentruntimes`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n14: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n15: - **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n16: - **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `AgentRuntime`\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n19: - **GIVEN** a typed client for `AgentRuntime`\n20: - **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type\n21: - **THEN** resource name is `agentruntimes` in plural form\n22: \n23: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeSpec structure with required fields\n24: \n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct with required fields: `PodTemplate` of type `*SandboxTemplate`, `SessionTimeout` of type `*metav1.Duration`, and `MaxSessionDuration` of type `*metav1.Duration`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Spec requires pod template\n28: - **GIVEN** a new `AgentRuntime` object being created\n29: - **WHEN** the spec is populated\n30: - **THEN** `PodTemplate` must be non-nil and contains the sandbox pod template\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Duration fields use metav1 types\n33: - **GIVEN** an existing `AgentRuntime` with timeouts configured\n34: - **WHEN** the spec is serialized to YAML\n35: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` and `MaxSessionDuration` serialize as duration strings\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeStatus with conditions support\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct with optional `Conditions` field of type `[]metav1.Condition` for tracking runtime state transitions.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Status conditions are optional\n42: - **GIVEN** a newly created `AgentRuntime` resource\n43: - **WHEN** status is initially empty\n44: - **THEN** resource creation succeeds without requiring conditions\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Condition updates follow Kubernetes conventions\n47: - **GIVEN** a controller managing `AgentRuntime` lifecycle\n48: - **WHEN** transitioning between states (e.g., Creating → Running)\n49: - **THEN** conditions are added with appropriate types, reasons, and transition timestamps\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeList type for collection operations\n52: \n53: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeList` as a standard Kubernetes list type containing `[]AgentRuntime` items and standard list metadata.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: List type supports pagination\n56: - **GIVEN** multiple `AgentRuntime` resources in a namespace\n57: - **WHEN** `List` operation is called with `ListOptions.Limit`\n58: - **THEN** response returns an `AgentRuntimeList` with `Continue` token when more items exist\n59: \n60: ### Requirement: Scheme registration for serialization\n61: \n62: The system SHALL register `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types in the Kubernetes scheme for proper JSON/YAML serialization and deserialization.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: YAML deserialization produces correct Go types\n65: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: AgentRuntime` in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group\n66: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded using the registered scheme\n67: - **THEN** an `AgentRuntime` struct instance is created with correct field mappings\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: List kind maps to AgentRuntimeList\n70: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: AgentRuntimeList`\n71: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded\n72: - **THEN** an `AgentRuntimeList` struct instance is created with items as `[]AgentRuntime`\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: CRD subresources support\n75: \n76: The system SHALL enable status subresource on `AgentRuntime` to allow independent updates to status without modifying spec.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Status update does not modify spec\n79: - **GIVEN** an existing `AgentRuntime` with both spec and status\n80: - **WHEN** a status-only update is performed via API server\n81: - **THEN** only status fields change and spec remains unmodified\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Status and spec have independent versioning\n84: - **GIVEN** a controller updating status\n85: - **WHEN** status changes multiple times\n86: - **THEN** each status update increments `metadata.generation` independently of spec modifications\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Default values for spec fields\n89: \n90: The system SHALL define kubebuilder markers to set default values: `SessionTimeout` defaults to `\"15m\"` and `MaxSessionDuration` defaults to `\"8h\"`.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Missing timeout fields receive defaults\n93: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` created without explicit timeout values\n94: - **WHEN** the resource is created via API\n95: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` is set to `15m` and `MaxSessionDuration` to `8h` automatically\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Explicit values override defaults\n98: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` created with custom timeout values\n99: - **WHEN** the resource is created\n100: - **THEN** the explicit values are preserved and defaults are not applied\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: OpenAPI validation for spec fields\n103: \n104: The system SHALL generate OpenAPI v3 schema for `AgentRuntime` to enable validation of field types, required fields, and constraints.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Required field validation\n107: - **GIVEN** a request creating `AgentRuntime` without required `PodTemplate`\n108: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n109: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating `podTemplate` is required\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Type validation for duration fields\n112: - **GIVEN** a request creating `AgentRuntime` with invalid duration format\n113: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n114: - **THEN** validation fails with error about invalid duration format\n115: \n116: ### Requirement: Print columns for kubectl readability\n117: \n118: The system SHALL configure additional printer columns for `kubectl get` output, including `Age` derived from `metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Age column displays correctly\n121: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` resource that was created 5 minutes ago\n122: - **WHEN** `kubectl get agentruntimes` is executed\n123: - **THEN** the Age column shows `5m` or equivalent time duration\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: CRD status storage optimization\n126: \n127: The system SHALL use status subresource to ensure status updates are stored efficiently and do not trigger spec reconciliation unnecessarily.\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Frequent status updates\n130: - **GIVEN** a controller updating `AgentRuntime` status every 30 seconds\n131: - **WHEN** multiple status updates occur\n132: - **THEN** each update only writes to status subresource and does not trigger full reconciliation\n133: \n134: ### Requirement: Type registration in code-generation\n135: \n136: The system SHALL ensure `AgentRuntime` types are included in the client-go code-generation pipeline to produce typed clients, informers, and listers.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Typed client operations work\n139: - **GIVEN** a `Clientset` instance from generated client-go code\n140: - **WHEN** calling `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create`\n141: - **THEN** the operation succeeds with proper type safety and returns an `AgentRuntime` pointer\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Informer factory recognizes AgentRuntime\n144: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` for the runtime API group\n145: - **WHEN** `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` is called\n146: - **THEN** an informer watching `agentruntimes` resources is returned\n147: \n148: ### Requirement: JSON tag naming convention\n149: \n150: The system SHALL use camelCase JSON tags for all fields to match Kubernetes API conventions and client-go expectations.\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: JSON serialization uses camelCase\n153: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` struct populated with Go fields\n154: - **WHEN** serialized to JSON\n155: - **THEN** the JSON keys are camelCase (e.g., `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `maxSessionDuration`)\n156: \n157: ### Requirement: DeepCopy methods for safety\n158: \n159: The system SHALL implement `DeepCopy`, `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopyObject` methods for `AgentRuntime` to support safe copying in controllers.\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: DeepCopy creates independent instance\n162: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` instance with populated fields\n163: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy` is called\n164: - **THEN** the returned copy is independent and modifications to the copy do not affect the original\n165: \n166: ### Requirement: Validation markers for fields\n167: \n168: The system SHALL use kubebuilder validation markers to enforce constraints on spec fields where applicable.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Duration fields validate format\n171: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `SessionTimeout` set to invalid duration\n172: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n173: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating invalid duration format\n174: \n175: ### Requirement: Label selector support for listing\n176: \n177: The system SHALL support standard Kubernetes label selectors when listing `AgentRuntime` resources.\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Label selector filters results\n180: - **GIVEN** multiple `AgentRuntime` resources with different labels\n181: - **WHEN** `List` is called with a label selector matching a specific label\n182: - **THEN** only resources matching the selector are returned\n183: \n184: ### Requirement: Watch support for controller integration\n185: \n186: The system SHALL support watch operations on `AgentRuntime` resources to enable controllers to react to changes efficiently.\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Watch events notify of changes\n189: - **GIVEN** a watch stream established on `AgentRuntime` resources\n190: - **WHEN** a new `AgentRuntime` is created\n191: - **THEN** the watch stream receives an ADDED event with the new resource\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 Delta Specification: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `AgentRuntime` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime type metadata and API group version\n\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `AgentRuntime`, and resource plural `agentruntimes`.\n\n#### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n- **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n- **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `AgentRuntime`\n\n#### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n- **GIVEN** a typed client for `AgentRuntime`\n- **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843260377,"end":1775843260390}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843260396,"sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","part":{"id":"prt_d7881b7be001MXN7q6PclnXbex","messageID":"msg_d7881a44e001zGrGozA8MnqczW","sessionID":"ses_2877ecc48ffeLfo6bU8734TLmk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c7b06c0f96024b7bae09866e8dc745d9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 Delta Specification: WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 基于生成的 client-go 库，构建 WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架，提供 REST API 用于管理 AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter 自定义资源，并支持健康检查、认证和错误处理。\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: HTTP 服务框架基础\n10: \n11: 系统 SHALL 在 `pkg/workloadmanager` 模块中构建基于标准库 `net/http` 的 HTTP 服务框架，支持路由注册、中间件链和优雅关闭。\n12: \n13: #### 场景: 创建 HTTP 服务器实例\n14: \n15: **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager` 包已存在  \n16: **WHEN** 初始化 HTTP 服务器  \n17: **THEN** 创建 `Server` 结构体，包含 `*http.Server`、路由注册表、中间件链配置和 shutdown channel\n18: \n19: ```go\n20: type Server struct {\n21:     httpServer   *http.Server\n22:     router       *mux.Router\n23:     middlewares  []Middleware\n24:     client       *clientset.Clientset\n25:     shutdownCh   chan struct{}\n26:     config       *Config\n27: }\n28: \n29: type Middleware func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n30: ```\n31: \n32: #### 场景: 启动和优雅关闭\n33: \n34: **GIVEN** Server 实例已配置  \n35: **WHEN** 调用 `Start()` 和 `Shutdown()` 方法  \n36: **THEN** 服务器监听配置的端口和地址，shutdown 时等待现有请求完成或超时\n37: \n38: ```go\n39: func (s *Server) Start(ctx context.Context) error\n40: func (s *Server) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ### Requirement: 路由注册和分发\n44: \n45: 系统 SHALL 支持基于 path 和 HTTP 方法的路由注册，使用第三方路由库（如 `gorilla/mux`）实现灵活的路由匹配。\n46: \n47: #### 场景: 注册 AgentRuntime 路由\n48: \n49: **GIVEN** Server 实例已创建  \n50: **WHEN** 注册 AgentRuntime 资源的路由  \n51: **THEN** 为 CRUD 操作创建标准 REST 路由\n52: \n53: ```\n54: GET    /apis/v1/agentruntimes              - List\n55: POST   /apis/v1/agentruntimes              - Create\n56: GET    /apis/v1/agentruntimes/{name}       - Get\n57: PUT    /apis/v1/agentruntimes/{name}       - Update\n58: PATCH  /apis/v1/agentruntimes/{name}       - Patch\n59: DELETE /apis/v1/agentruntimes/{name}       - Delete\n60: ```\n61: \n62: #### 场景: 注册 CodeInterpreter 路由\n63: \n64: **GIVEN** Server 实例已创建  \n65: **WHEN** 注册 CodeInterpreter 资源的路由  \n66: **THEN** 为 CRUD 操作创建标准 REST 路由\n67: \n68: ```\n69: GET    /apis/v1/codeinterpreters           - List\n70: POST   /apis/v1/codeinterpreters           - Create\n71: GET    /apis/v1/codeinterpreters/{name}    - Get\n72: PUT    /apis/v1/codeinterpreters/{name}    - Update\n73: PATCH  /apis/v1/codeinterpreters/{name}    - Patch\n74: DELETE /apis/v1/codeinterpreters/{name}    - Delete\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: 中间件系统\n78: \n79: 系统 SHALL 实现可插拔的中间件系统，支持认证、日志记录、请求追踪、错误恢复和 CORS。\n80: \n81: #### 场景: 认证中间件\n82: \n83: **GIVEN** HTTP 请求进入服务  \n84: **WHEN** 请求到达需要认证的路由  \n85: **THEN** 验证请求头中的认证信息，无效时返回 401 Unauthorized\n86: \n87: ```go\n88: func AuthenticationMiddleware(authProvider AuthProvider) Middleware\n89: ```\n90: \n91: #### 场景: 日志中间件\n92: \n93: **GIVEN** HTTP 请求进入服务  \n94: **WHEN** 请求经过日志中间件  \n95: **THEN** 记录请求方法、路径、状态码、延迟和请求 ID\n96: \n97: ```go\n98: func LoggingMiddleware(logger logr.Logger) Middleware\n99: ```\n100: \n101: #### 场景: 恢复中间件\n102: \n103: **GIVEN** HTTP 请求处理中发生 panic  \n104: **WHEN** panic 被 RecoveryMiddleware 捕获  \n105: **THEN** 返回 500 Internal Server Error 并记录 panic 信息\n106: \n107: ```go\n108: func RecoveryMiddleware(logger logr.Logger) Middleware\n109: ```\n110: \n111: #### 场景: CORS 中间件\n112: \n113: **GIVEN** 浏览器发起跨域请求  \n114: **WHEN** 请求经过 CORS 中间件  \n115: **THEN** 响应包含适当的 CORS 头（Access-Control-Allow-Origin 等）\n116: \n117: ```go\n118: func CORSMiddleware(allowedOrigins []string) Middleware\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### Requirement: HTTP 处理器（Handlers）\n122: \n123: 系统 SHALL 为每个 CRUD 操作实现处理器函数，使用 client-go 库与 Kubernetes API 交互。\n124: \n125: #### 场景: 创建 AgentRuntime\n126: \n127: **GIVEN** 有效的 AgentRuntime 请求体  \n128: **WHEN** POST /apis/v1/agentruntimes  \n129: **THEN** 验证请求体，调用 client-go Create，返回创建的资源（201 Created）或错误\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: func (h *AgentRuntimeHandler) Create(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n133: ```\n134: \n135: #### 场景: 获取 AgentRuntime\n136: \n137: **GIVEN** AgentRuntime 名称存在  \n138: **WHEN** GET /apis/v1/agentruntimes/{name}  \n139: **THEN** 调用 client-go Get，返回资源（200 OK）或 404 Not Found\n140: \n141: ```go\n142: func (h *AgentRuntimeHandler) Get(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n143: ```\n144: \n145: #### 场景: 列出 AgentRuntime\n146: \n147: **GIVEN** Kubernetes 集群中有多个 AgentRuntime  \n148: **WHEN** GET /apis/v1/agentruntimes  \n149: **THEN** 调用 client-go List，支持 label selector 和 field selector 查询，返回列表（200 OK）\n150: \n151: ```go\n152: func (h *AgentRuntimeHandler) List(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n153: ```\n154: \n155: #### 场景: 更新 AgentRuntime\n156: \n157: **GIVEN** AgentRuntime 名称存在且请求体有效  \n158: **WHEN** PUT /apis/v1/agentruntimes/{name}  \n159: **THEN** 调用 client-go Update，返回更新后的资源（200 OK）或错误\n160: \n161: ```go\n162: func (h *AgentRuntimeHandler) Update(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n163: ```\n164: \n165: #### 场景: 删除 AgentRuntime\n166: \n167: **GIVEN** AgentRuntime 名称存在  \n168: **WHEN** DELETE /apis/v1/agentruntimes/{name}  \n169: **THEN** 调用 client-go Delete，返回 204 No Content 或错误\n170: \n171: ```go\n172: func (h *AgentRuntimeHandler) Delete(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n173: ```\n174: \n175: #### 场景: CodeInterpreter CRUD 操作\n176: \n177: **GIVEN** CodeInterpreter 处理器已注册  \n178: **WHEN** 执行 CodeInterpreter 的 CRUD 操作  \n179: **THEN** 行为与 AgentRuntime 一致，使用 `codeinterpreter` 资源类型\n180: \n181: ### Requirement: 健康检查端点\n182: \n183: 系统 SHALL 提供健康检查端点，用于 K8s liveness 和 readiness probes。\n184: \n185: #### 场景: Liveness probe\n186: \n187: **GIVEN** WorkloadManager Pod 正在运行  \n188: **WHEN** GET /health (liveness)  \n189: **THEN** 返回 200 OK 和健康状态\n190: \n191: ```go\n192: func (s *Server) LivenessProbe(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n193: ```\n194: \n195: #### 场景: Readiness probe\n196: \n197: **GIVEN** WorkloadManager 已准备好接收请求  \n198: **WHEN** GET /ready (readiness)  \n199: **THEN** 检查与 Kubernetes API 的连接性，返回 200 OK 或 503\n200: \n201: ```go\n202: func (s *Server) ReadinessProbe(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n203: ```\n204: \n205: ### Requirement: 错误处理和响应\n206: \n207: 系统 SHALL 实现统一的错误处理和 JSON 响应格式。\n208: \n209: #### 场景: 错误响应格式\n210: \n211: **GIVEN** HTTP 处理中发生错误  \n212: **WHEN** 返回错误响应  \n213: **THEN** 使用统一的 JSON 错误格式\n214: \n215: ```json\n216: {\n217:   \"code\": \"RuntimeNotFound\",\n218:   \"message\": \"AgentRuntime 'my-runtime' not found\",\n219:   \"details\": {\n220:     \"name\": \"my-runtime\",\n221:     \"namespace\": \"default\"\n222:   }\n223: }\n224: ```\n225: \n226: #### 场景: Kubernetes API 错误转换\n227: \n228: **GIVEN** client-go 返回 Kubernetes API 错误  \n229: **WHEN** 错误传递到 HTTP 层  \n230: **THEN** 将 Kubernetes 错误转换为适当的 HTTP 状态码和错误消息\n231: \n232: ```go\n233: func K8sErrorToHTTP(err error) (int, *ErrorResponse)\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ### Requirement: 配置管理\n237: \n238: 系统 SHALL 支持从环境变量和配置文件加载配置。\n239: \n240: #### 场景: 加载配置\n241: \n242: **GIVEN** 环境变量和配置文件已设置  \n243: **WHEN** 服务器启动  \n244: **THEN** 从以下来源加载配置并合并：环境变量、配置文件、默认值\n245: \n246: ```go\n247: type Config struct {\n248:     ListenAddr     string\n249:     Port           int\n250:     KubeConfigPath string\n251:     LogLevel       string\n252:     MetricsEnabled bool\n253:     RedisAddr      string\n254:     RedisPassword  string\n255: }\n256: \n257: func LoadConfig() (*Config, error)\n258: ```\n259: \n260: ### Requirement: 指标和追踪\n261: \n262: 系统 SHALL 集成 Prometheus 指标和分布式追踪支持。\n263: \n264: #### 场景: Prometheus 指标\n265: \n266: **GIVEN** HTTP 请求处理中  \n267: **WHEN** 记录指标  \n268: **THEN** 暴露标准 HTTP 指标（请求计数、延迟、活跃连接）和业务指标\n269: \n270: ```\n271: GET /metrics - Prometheus metrics endpoint\n272: ```\n273: \n274: ```go\n275: func MetricsMiddleware(reg prometheus.Registerer) Middleware\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### Requirement: 请求验证\n279: \n280: 系统 SHALL 在处理器之前验证请求数据。\n281: \n282: #### 场景: 请求体验证\n283: \n284: **GIVEN** HTTP 请求包含 JSON body  \n285: **WHEN** 请求进入处理器  \n286: **THEN** 验证 JSON 格式和必需字段，无效时返回 400 Bad Request\n287: \n288: ```go\n289: func ValidateRequestBody(obj interface{}) error\n290: func ValidationMiddleware(schema validation.Schema) Middleware\n291: ```\n292: \n293: ### Requirement: 客户端注入\n294: \n295: 系统 SHALL 支持依赖注入 client-go 客户端到处理器。\n296: \n297: #### 场景: 注入 Kubernetes 客户端\n298: \n299: **GIVEN** Server 已配置 kubeconfig  \n300: **WHEN** 创建处理器  \n301: **THEN** 将 `*clientset.Clientset` 注入到处理器结构体中\n302: \n303: ```go\n304: type AgentRuntimeHandler struct {\n305:     client  *clientset.Clientset\n306:     logger  logr.Logger\n307:     metrics *Metrics\n308: }\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: Watch 支持\n312: \n313: 系统 SHALL 支持通过 Server-Sent Events (SSE) 或 WebSocket 监听资源变更。\n314: \n315: #### 场景: Watch AgentRuntime 变更\n316: \n317: **GIVEN** 客户端需要监听 AgentRuntime 变更  \n318: **WHEN** GET /apis/v1/agentruntimes?watch=true  \n319: **THEN** 使用 client-go Watch API，通过 SSE 流式传输变更事件\n320: \n321: ```go\n322: func (h *AgentRuntimeHandler) Watch(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n323: ```\n324: \n325: ### Requirement: 文件组织\n326: \n327: 系统 SHALL 按职责分离文件，组织 `pkg/workloadmanager` 模块。\n328: \n329: #### 场景: 文件结构清晰分离\n330: \n331: **GIVEN** pkg/workloadmanager 模块需要组织代码  \n332: **WHEN** 创建文件结构  \n333: **THEN** 按职责分离文件：\n334: \n335: ```\n336: pkg/workloadmanager/\n337: ├── server.go              # Server 结构体和启动/关闭逻辑\n338: ├── router.go              # 路由注册和分发\n339: ├── middleware.go          # 中间件实现\n340: ├── handlers.go            # HTTP 处理器接口和基础实现\n341: ├── agentruntime.go        # AgentRuntime 处理器\n342: ├── codeinterpreter.go     # CodeInterpreter 处理器\n343: ├── health.go              # 健康检查端点\n344: ├── response.go            # 响应格式化和错误处理\n345: ├── config.go              # 配置加载和管理\n346: ├── metrics.go             # Prometheus 指标\n347: ├── validation.go          # 请求验证\n348: └── errors.go              # 错误类型和转换\n349: ```\n350: \n351: ## 最终验证\n352: \n353: ### 场景: 端到端集成测试\n354: \n355: **GIVEN** WorkloadManager HTTP 服务已启动并连接到测试 Kubernetes 集群  \n356: **WHEN** 执行完整的 CRUD 操作序列  \n357: **THEN** 所有操作成功返回预期响应，指标正确记录，日志完整输出\n358: \n359: ### 场景: 并发请求处理\n360: \n361: **GIVEN** WorkloadManager HTTP 服务已启动  \n362: **WHEN** 发送多个并发请求  \n363: **THEN** 服务器正确处理所有请求，无竞态条件，响应时间在预期范围内\n364: \n365: ### 场景: 错误场景覆盖\n366: \n367: **GIVEN** WorkloadManager HTTP 服务已启动  \n368: **WHEN** 发送各种错误请求（无效 JSON、不存在的资源、权限错误等）  \n369: **THEN** 服务器返回适当的错误响应，状态码正确，错误消息清晰\n370: \n371: ### 场景: 资源清理\n372: \n373: **GIVEN** WorkloadManager 优雅关闭  \n374: **WHEN** 调用 Shutdown()  \n375: **THEN** 所有连接正确关闭，无资源泄漏，进程退出码为 0\n\n(End of file - total 375 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 Delta Specification: WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n\n## Purpose\n\n基于生成的 client-go 库，构建 WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架，提供 REST API 用于管理 AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter 自定义资源，并支持健康检查、认证和错误处理。\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: HTTP 服务框架基础\n\n系统 SHALL 在 `pkg/workloadmanager` 模块中构建基于标准库 `net/http` 的 HTTP 服务框架，支持路由注册、中间件链和优雅关闭。\n\n#### 场景: 创建 HTTP 服务器实例\n\n**GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager` 包已存在  \n**WHEN** 初始化 HTTP 服务器  \n**THEN** 创建 `Server` 结构体，包含 `*http.Server`、路由注册表、中间件链配置和 shutdown channel\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843260380,"end":1775843260393}}}}
